  <h2><a href="../node/92" title="Two papers accepted to SenSys 2008">Two papers accepted to SenSys 2008</a></h2>

      <span class="submitted">Tue, 07/22/2008 - 19:12 — Matt Welsh</span>
  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <div style="width: 100px" class="image-attach-teaser"><a href="../node/92"><img src="http://fiji.eecs.harvard.edu/sites/default/files/images/raleigh-skyline.thumbnail.jpg" alt="raleigh-skyline.jpg" title="raleigh-skyline.jpg"  class="image image-thumbnail " width="100" height="62" /></a></div>
Our group has two papers accepted to the upcoming <a href="http://sensys.acm.org/2008/">6th ACM Conference on Embedded Networked Sensor Systems (SenSys'08)</a>. They are:

<ul>
<li> <a href="../biblio/citekey/pixie-sensys08"><b>Resource Aware Programming in the Pixie OS</b></a>, Konrad Lorincz, Bor-rong Chen, Jason Waterman, Geoff Werner-Allen, and Matt Welsh.
</li><li> <a href="../biblio/citekey/lance-sensys08"><b>Lance: Optimizing High-Resolution Signal Collection in Wireless Sensor Networks</b></a>, Geoff Werner-Allen, Stephen Dawson-Haggerty, and Matt Welsh.
</li></ul>

<p>
Click the links above for full text.</p>  </div>

